Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.25,0:17:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,create arms is being you know uh people are for guns and against guns and uh I'm\Na retired policeman and I've always carried a gun and I wondered you know it seems like from the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,from my point of view, that the freedom of the country\Nis important for people to be able to bear arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.73,0:17:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I don't know, because there's so many people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.45,0:17:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,seem to be against guns, which position is more true\Nor right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.74,0:17:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, from what position?\NThe right to bear arms, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.92,0:17:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just, we have permission to calibrate it.\NIt's over 450, 480, 500, 490, 495, it calibrates around 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.13,0:17:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, that would be intellectually correct\Nand certainly would fit into the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:18:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Founding Fathers, that we should have\Nall the freedoms possible, except when to do so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.06,0:18:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,would put others at grave risk or cause them\Nto lose their freedom, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.98,0:18:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be my readout.\NI'll put a link on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NBeen a lot of years since I packed that .45.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.18,0:18:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Navy would stand watch, you know,\Nwe were in the South Pacific, you didn't have to wear
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,many clothes, it was so hot, so I'd be on night watch\Ntotaled to four or something, and all you had on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.45,0:18:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,was your shorts and your duty belt with a loaded .45\Ncaliber and your holster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.93,0:18:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A holster and your holster.\NAnd your holster and your shorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.77,0:18:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.81,0:19:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, my question is regarding demonic energy.\NAnd I just wanna know what the first step
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in eliminating that kind of energy\Nand how it influences my actions and how to get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you lead a pure life.\NAnd if you lead a pure life, the negative energies
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.49,0:19:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,will leave you because you become distasteful to them.\NSo, what you do is lead a pure life yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.43,0:19:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Surround yourself with positive, pure energy.\NAssociate with people that are spiritually advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.62,0:19:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang out with spiritual groups.\NThere's nothing demons hate worse than angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.34,0:19:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang out with angels and the demons will leave you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NFlies always hang around garbage, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:20:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah.\NSo, you lead as pure a life as you can yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.70,0:20:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDemons don't like spirituality and purity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.83,0:20:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those things.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.49,0:20:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask if the person on that card\Ncan accurately answer questions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,through muscle testing with a pendulum?\NI can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.24,0:20:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?\NHm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI didn't work with the pendulums and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.48,0:20:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all different energy of, you know?\NOh, well can muscle testing be done with a pendulum?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Like-\NWhy don't you just do muscle testing with muscle testing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and pendulums with pendulums?\NSo-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you want to mix them up?\NIt's not the same thing exact,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.05,0:21:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not called muscle testing, or-\NPendulum is one thing, muscle testing is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.22,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're both accurate,\Nyou should get the same answers both ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Оokay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay.\Nanswer both ways can I ask one more question how do you recognize demonic energy and like yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.50,0:21:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or your friends or whatever like if like if you're questioning whether you or your friends are\Npossessed you know by demons how could you recognize oh I wouldn't play with that game
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.94,0:21:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you could use the same as you do with any other you know I'd say this person is possessed by evil\Ndemons yes or no or if you use the pendulum also your intuition your spiritual intuition should
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:22:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you although some are very sophisticated in the way they present themselves some come on\Nvery holy in fact when people come on super holy I'm always suspicious of them if you're so holy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to do the whole like you're a movie movie holy person you know what I'm saying\Nyou're just integrous because that's who you are so there's no need to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.45,0:22:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,love you\Nlay it on people you know two-foot-high crucifixes a foot across and long robes and the sandals and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.38,0:23:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jesus haircut you know forget all that okay thank you can I ask if you know this person\Nyes you talk about giving people a shot of love what
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.78,0:23:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I\Nfound is that sometimes you'll give people a shot of love and out of the blue all of a sudden you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.90,0:23:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,give them an overdose in which case they will either start crying and come up and give you a\Nhug or they go into a panic their eyes get big and they went to a panic and they will avoid you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.82,0:23:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is there any way that you can learn how to give them let's say five CC's instead of ten thousand\NCC's don't give or receive love it's not a commodity just be a part of it and it's not a commodity just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.54,0:24:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,be what you are period just be what you are walk around the beetle rather than squish them you don't\Nhave to lean lean over and kiss them scare the beetle if you try to kiss it yeah now if you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,respect the integrity of others and treat them integrously that that is loving to treat people\Nintegrously to begin with yes you just tore my ear off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.50,0:24:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I love your laugh\NI love your laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.28,0:24:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I love your laugh\NI love your laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.17,0:24:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for being here Dr. Hawkins\NMy question is I teach yoga in an adolescent psych ward and in the prison system for teens
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.17,0:24:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You teach yoga where?\NIn the prison system for teenagers and in the children in psych wards at a children's hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.58,0:24:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what would be my best approach with them because a lot of them are brilliant children\NAre really what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.76,0:24:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Are brilliant children\NYes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.82,0:25:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can I do to help get them to the next place of health mental health?\NWell I can't answer it the way you're presenting it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.79,0:25:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about yoga that's one thing mental health is another\NI know people who do yoga right and left for you know years in their careers they're in a loon
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.51,0:25:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't so crazy they wouldn't be doing yoga around the clock for years in and years out\NYoga is good if you're going to be a dance teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.89,0:25:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there some physical things that I can help them with with their bodies?\NBecause they're not in their bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.00,0:26:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's not using their bodies right?\NThey're not in their bodies you know the mentally handicapped are not in their bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.00,0:26:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can she do?\NWhat are you supposed to be doing with them teaching them yoga?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.00,0:26:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just doing I'm doing yoga with them but the thing that they absolutely love is relaxation\NSo in the relaxation it gets them to the next place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.00,0:26:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it are you hired as a therapist or yoga teacher or what?\NYoga teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.00,0:26:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A yoga teacher?\NYes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.00,0:26:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so why don't you just teach them yoga?\NWell she's saying in the relaxation and the cool down there's certain terms that you talk about to relax them after they've had this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.55,0:26:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well whatever if that's the yoga then you do the yoga\NYou know you could maybe inspire them with wonderful thoughts is what I would say
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.48,0:26:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe that would take advantage of that\NYou could take beautiful thoughts rather than where their mind has been
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.48,0:26:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay\NThat might help
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.67,0:27:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay great\NYou know like a thought like that God loves you all the time no matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.17,0:27:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or anything like that\NYeah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.17,0:27:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that would help you know if you say that in a certain way you know without mentioning God\NIt can still be an uplifting experience in a cool down
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.17,0:27:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right\NYeah I just tell people you're lovable just as you are you don't have to be any different for God to love you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.23,0:28:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome great I will thank you thank you very much\NAlright
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.34,0:28:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you\NThank you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.22,0:28:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping things simple answers most questions\NAlright
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.68,0:28:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to teach them yoga then just teach them yoga\NNice to meet you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.89,0:28:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you\NYes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.89,0:28:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello it's nice to meet you\NI just want to ask you what is the soul in relation to the one self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.53,0:28:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The soul is the self with a capital S\NBut there are many souls
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.53,0:28:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right\NAnd only one self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.53,0:28:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean there's many souls?\NDo you have multiple souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.53,0:28:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No\NI hope not
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.92,0:28:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No when he says self with a capital S\NSelf with a capital S that is the higher self
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.95,0:29:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher self and then there's self with a small s that's the ego\NOkay
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.49,0:29:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because of A Course in Miracles when it said that there's only one son of God\NAnd then it splits into many egos and there are many souls
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.88,0:29:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I can't put it together\NSo I can't put it together
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.88,0:29:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a breakdown in the language\NThe languaging oh yes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.62,0:29:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the languaging\NAre you talking about the workbook or the textbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.61,0:29:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's German so it's a breakdown in language\NYou're talking about the textbook or the workbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.61,0:29:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The textbook\NYes the textbook calibrates less than the workbook for this very reason
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.76,0:29:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook calibrates to 600 the textbook calibrates 550\NHmm
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.36,0:30:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there is this hypothetical languaging\NThe experiential reality is not the way it's languaged in that book
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.39,0:30:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay\NThank you very much
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.52,0:30:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah the workbook is much harder than that\NThere is only one self with a capital S which is divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.80,0:30:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So divinity cannot be multiple it's one\NSo the multiple is the expression of the one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.83,0:30:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah\NBut you don't need to understand it intellectually anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.66,0:30:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is only one soul\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.66,0:30:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one soul that we share together?\NNo
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.88,0:30:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No\NThere is only one soul within you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.88,0:30:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah\NThere is only one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.17,0:30:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm\NAh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.62,0:30:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one self with a capital S and that is the presence of God\NSee
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.62,0:31:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God is each one is experiencing it as the self with a capital S\NBut there is only one divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.76,0:31:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm\NEach one experiences it as the presence of divinity within
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.60,0:31:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one sunshine shining\NEach person experiences the radiance of the sun somewhat differently
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.00,0:31:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean they are different suns\NIt just means each one is experiencing the sun from their own perceptual intellectual level
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.57,0:31:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes\NHmm
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.57,0:31:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much\NHmm
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.57,0:31:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It clarifies it\NYes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.76,0:31:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm\NYou go six inches this way for the camera
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.42,0:31:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to do?\NYou go six inches this way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.42,0:31:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Six inches?\NYeah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God man\NNext thing you want a foot
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.42,0:31:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha\NFirst they ask six inches then they want a foot
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.67,0:31:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how it goes\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.50,0:31:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then your arm\NThen your legs
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.60,0:32:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then your shoulder\NHa
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.23,0:32:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha\NIf it ain't one thing it's the other
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.96,0:32:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I\NI
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.15,0:32:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes\NI'd like to ask you to bless this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.43,0:32:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd just like to express gratitude\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Buddha.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.47,0:32:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do with it?\NHe wants you to bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.57,0:32:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.09,0:32:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to bless this Buddha and resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.21,0:32:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is blessed.\NAmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.95,0:32:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.68,0:32:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just want to express gratitude.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.48,0:33:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, first of all, I want to say thank you very much.\NAnd I have a question on guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.25,0:33:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you transcend experience when you experientially feel like...\NI'm not understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.76,0:33:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak slow and near the microphone.\NWhen there is experience that you have intentionally gone against the self,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.83,0:33:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you transcend the guilt from that?\NThe echoes are bearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.69,0:33:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When you intentionally go against the self, and you know you have,\Nhow do you transcend that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.26,0:34:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because she feels guilt over that.\NOr you have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.16,0:34:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to forgive yourself and decide to do better.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.67,0:34:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.11,0:34:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You decide that you're only human, and human does the best it can.\NAnd it's not perfect in its expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're tolerant and benign.\NYou have a benign attitude towards your own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.85,0:34:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an honor to be here.\NI just wanted to ask you if you could expound more on surrendering the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.51,0:34:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment to self-sabotage.\NI'm not reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.95,0:34:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-sabotage.\NWhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.03,0:34:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrendering attachment to the...\NSurrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.61,0:35:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To where?\NWhat do you mean by self-sabotage?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.73,0:35:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the ego's...\NIt seems like the ego's always trying to freeze it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.80,0:35:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of perfection?\NError?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.16,0:35:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt's like nothing's ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.43,0:35:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, obviously nothing's ever good enough for it.\NAnd then it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.13,0:35:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to surrender the programming behind that.\NI don't hear what he's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.83,0:35:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The programming behind what?\NPerfection?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Like shame.\NHe's carrying shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.23,0:35:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHe wants to know how does he overcome shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.69,0:35:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he should be ashamed of feeling shame all the time.\NYou accept the fact that you're only immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.93,0:36:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you're prone to error.\NAnd yes, forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.74,0:36:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you pray to do better.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.44,0:36:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's almost impossible to live in this world\Nand not regret some action, be ashamed of some action.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.06,0:36:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So you forgive yourself that it's just part of being human.\NAnd that's the reason we're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.30,0:36:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is to overcome these defects of character\Nand transcend them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.04,0:36:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NSo you have to be benign towards yourself as well as others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.74,0:36:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See, so it's not only to stop being judgmental towards others,\Nbut to stop being judgmental about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.98,0:36:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, you know, out of wisdom,\Nyou decide you won't go in that direction anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.28,0:37:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you accord yourself the same forgiveness\Nthat you would someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.83,0:37:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone else did that,\Nwould you be willing to forgive them?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.49,0:37:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or no?\NIf you're willing to forgive them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.77,0:37:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then you forgive yourself.\NFor being stupid and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.00,0:37:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou accord yourself the same forgiveness you would
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.33,0:37:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to your brother, you know.\NAnd say, look, he's an imperfect human.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.72,0:37:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's doing the best he can.\NAnd so we forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.05,0:37:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We give them in Christ's name.\NAnd ask God to help us do better next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.31,0:38:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NI first want to shake your hand and her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.09,0:38:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?\NWait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.19,0:38:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak slowly, go ahead.\NI first want to shake your hand and her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.75,0:38:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?\NWho wants to shake your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.06,0:38:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Or touch your hand.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.43,0:38:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NWe're having really bad audio feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.38,0:38:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, this is a sign already.\NMy question is, what is the purpose of a mediator?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.24,0:38:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to concentrate on what I'm saying.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.96,0:38:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the purpose of a mediator in what regard?\NIn the sense of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.90,0:38:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ or Buddha or Krishna?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.38,0:38:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The ordinary mortal would not have the temerity to address divinity directly.\NAnd therefore, Jesus Christ, or an aspect of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.59,0:39:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,acts in your behalf as your advocate.\NPleads your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.84,0:39:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So for Christians, Jesus Christ will say to God\Nthat this is one of my flaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.21,0:39:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have taught him, and I will be looking,\Nand I'll be answerable for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.08,0:39:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you screw up, Jesus goes to God about you.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.52,0:39:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're advocate.\NNow, there is also a similar representation of Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.62,0:39:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In Lotusland Buddhism,\NVala Katsavara is that aspect of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.72,0:39:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that will speak in your behalf before the ultimate.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.14,0:39:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.45,0:39:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you pray to Jesus Christ as Savior,\Nhow does he save you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.85,0:40:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He speaks for you before the Father.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.53,0:40:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.66,0:40:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a lawyer guarantees to the court\Nthat you will come up with the fine next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.17,0:40:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you both very much, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.75,0:40:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been inspirational.\NI want to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.25,0:40:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.29,0:40:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.39,0:40:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.67,0:40:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.79,0:40:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.87,0:40:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.05,0:40:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnd I love you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.59,0:40:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThe following question is submitted by Rob Corr
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.19,0:40:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from the consciousnessproject.org.\NWhen we go through the process of enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.09,0:40:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, leaving the world,\Nlosing interest in worldly things, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.09,0:40:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,will it be something we realize why it's happening?\NAnd if it occurs to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.49,0:40:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I'm losing interest in worldly involvement,\Nis that an ego trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.54,0:41:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThat is one indication.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.66,0:41:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have less and less interest in the world\Nand the values of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.02,0:41:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual values become predominant.\NSo the fact that you can make money at something
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.49,0:41:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is interesting, but it's not sufficiently interesting\Nfor you to change your lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.12,0:41:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I could make more money practicing medicine right now\Nthan sitting here talking to you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.70,0:41:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?\NAgreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.10,0:41:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.18,0:41:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's irrelevant.\NBecause, you know, you did that then and you do this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.58,0:41:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NSo what's suitable for one phase of life
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.74,0:41:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,may not be suitable for another.\NThere's a phase of life where you should be out there
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.78,0:41:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,working your butt off to, you know, pay for everything and all.\NAnd then once you've accomplished that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.47,0:41:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and realize I can do that anytime,\Nthen you may move on to the next level, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.89,0:42:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're doing may be right for a certain time\Nof your life, but not at another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.03,0:42:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.27,0:42:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAngel Lewis sends her love.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.27,0:42:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.30,0:42:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, is there any place that God is not?\NIs there any place that God is not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.69,0:42:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.69,0:42:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you both for the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.69,0:42:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NIt's just remember they're all your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.69,0:42:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your...\NThat was Greg Daniels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.72,0:42:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Greg Daniels.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.31,0:42:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.80,0:42:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.24,0:43:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.77,0:43:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.77,0:43:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.\NI'll take your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.90,0:43:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, here.\NI need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.99,0:43:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, here.\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.99,0:43:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI didn't answer for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.99,0:43:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI didn't ask for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.99,0:43:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.02,0:43:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to say thanks.\NAnd I wondered if I could shake your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.11,0:43:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.78,0:43:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming up and saying hello.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.78,0:43:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Straight to the question.\NMy question is about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.78,0:43:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,About a year and a half ago at one of your presentations was almost an off-the-cuff when\Nyou commented that...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.28,0:44:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment of our birth, the moment of our death is already established. Do you\Nrecall? The moment of your birth, the moment of your death is established. It's set. It's set. Yes. Could you elaborate on that? No. Oh. What more is there to say? Okay, can I put it into some context? No. Okay. You're asking
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.67,0:45:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,an abstract question. Is the moment of your death already preset? Okay. We have permission to ask this. Resist. The answer is yes. Resist. Well, may we conclude then from that? I accept that. You've already got the answer. Now, what is the question? Then health care just makes our life more pleasant. You're dealing with the hypothetical. You see, you're manufacturing a hypothetical rhetorical question with no reality. When you do, it'll leave. Bye.\NIt could be in a car wreck. Yeah. It could be all these other things. So health care is a waste of taxpayers' money because if you're going to croak, you're going to croak. Bye. That's the answer to my question. Hey, we finally got some sound. Thank you. Yeah, I say they're wasting money on these old guys. Their old crocs are going to go anyway. What the hell are you keeping them alive for? The longer they stay alive, the more it costs the taxpayer and Social Security.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.45,0:46:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a question. Yeah, we love your laughter so much. And I think you are the cutest and sweetest person in the world. Oh, my goodness. Can I have your hand? Yes. Yes. She's so right.\NI just want to say just thank you for being what you are. And I love you. And I need all the help I can get and.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.18,0:46:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just I'm very appreciative. Thank you very much. Yes. Hi. I have a question about resistance. I find that to move from one level to the other, I encounter an awful lot of resistance to doing the things I need to do that I know I need to do. And yet quite often I don't do them. Oh, do it some other lifetime.\NPardon? Do it some other lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.44,0:47:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you. Thank you very much. That's not good for me.\NIs he a mean old crab or what? Sometimes. You want him to change, right? Well, I think he wants to. No, I'm asking you. You want him to change, don't you? I see it all over your face. Oh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.44,0:47:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all right.\NNow, to make her happy, would you be willing to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.10,0:47:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I guess.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.10,0:47:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's working in that direction, at least you know he's trying, you know?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.05,0:47:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is somewhat different.\NI'm wondering if you'd share your thoughts about the atrocities in Rwanda around 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.69,0:47:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that something you would comment on?\NWhat was behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.05,0:47:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the question?\NThe atrocities in Rwanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.37,0:48:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Rwanda.\NWhere they took out all those people, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.57,0:48:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NWhat about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.93,0:48:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a genocide.\NIt was a genocide, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.63,0:48:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, too much that your comments on that.\NWhat is it that's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.45,0:48:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do...\NGenocide, well, in a general way, collective karma, there's collective karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.39,0:48:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A country, a community, an organization.\NJointly agrees to take certain behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.41,0:48:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that's in a negative direction, now they're karmically in debt, are they not?\NSo, they come back, and this time they experience a volcano, and it blows 3,000 people, all the smithers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.68,0:48:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's...\NOkay, we'll ask the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.82,0:48:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is such a thing as group karma.\NWhat is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.85,0:48:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Group karma.\NWell, we know that, but they were asking the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.23,0:48:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's group karma, where everybody agrees.\NIs in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.98,0:49:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In total agreement.\NThen there's a certain spiritual cost to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.40,0:49:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to undo that, the person may then come back in this lifetime and undo the karma, karmic debt they owe.\NIf you were one of those who persecuted and killed the Jews during World War II, you may have a certain karmic debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.89,0:49:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And may come back and yourself, perhaps, be killed.\NBecause of your ethnic origin, or religion, or race, or something, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.98,0:49:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people are always saying, how do all those innocent people, blah, blah, blah.\NAnd I always say, they aren't all innocent, or they wouldn't have been, you know, hot lava rained on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.78,0:49:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't innocent.\NThat's why they were turned into ashes in 18 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.52,0:50:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hot lava, you know, is at 3,000 degrees, will turn you into ashes in a matter of seconds.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.37,0:50:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's not just accidental that there is a pattern, a karmic pattern, in death and disaster,\Nand why certain groups always happen to be right where the disasters are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.18,0:50:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are they always right where a tsunami is happening?\NWhy aren't you on Jones Beach, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.18,0:50:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you very much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.07,0:50:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's a group, group karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.08,0:50:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, group karma.\NThat which you align yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.34,0:50:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you take on, you take on some of the karmic consequences of that with which you align yourself.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.02,0:51:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.41,0:51:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is around physical conditions in the body, specifically diabetes.\NIs it something that can be, I guess, cured, or can you actually complete the karma of it in this life, or in the body in this lifetime, and how?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.04,0:51:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in and of itself, it has no specific karma.\NThere's no karmic pattern that, you know, comes forth just as diabetes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.73,0:51:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's generally more genetic than anything else, you know?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.03,0:51:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd, of course, you do everything you can to transcend it using all the modalities that are available in today's world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.06,0:51:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which were not available, you know, decades ago.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.75,0:51:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.98,0:51:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for the work, both of you.\NIt's so, it touched me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.06,0:51:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd my question has to do with my own purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.14,0:51:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With your own what?\NPurpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.76,0:52:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.64,0:52:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had a landscaping company for 10 years, and I've been called to begin doing spiritual, like, healing work.\NAnd I've started that school, and my heart feels like it's just overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.05,0:52:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll get spontaneous pains and so forth in my body, and then they'll disappear.\NAnd.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.55,0:52:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I'm called to that work, and there's such a divinity with that.\NAnd I feel like I still have responsibilities to these other things that I've created in my landscaping business and my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.22,0:52:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, there's just such a part of me I could just let it go, you know?\NAnd, okay, bankruptcy, fine, whatever, you know, let it all go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.52,0:52:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think there's some fear there around, you know, perhaps even the karmic consequences of that.\NKarmic consequences of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.46,0:53:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Of not holding up to the obligations that I've created to date.\NYou're going to mow somebody's lawn for the next 30 years, and you feel guilty if you quit now?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.91,0:53:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a really good point.\NYou're seeing yourself as indispensable.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.02,0:53:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not indispensable.\NYou can do a trade-off.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.48,0:53:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not indispensable.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.76,0:53:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When I closed up my private practice, I found other doctors that would take on the patients, you know?\NI don't have to stay in practice forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.56,0:53:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to stay in practice forever.\NI found other doctors that would take them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.94,0:53:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.50,0:53:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.78,0:53:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can help them find another landscaper.\NSell the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.08,0:53:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\NThe camera's gone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.29,0:53:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The battery's loaded.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.48,0:54:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NMove the microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.50,0:54:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.48,0:54:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NThere's rocks in this box.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.34,0:54:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NThere's rocks in this box.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.46,0:54:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nyes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.70,0:54:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,oh they're hearts\Nthese are a gift from
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.88,0:54:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the boulder flock\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.52,0:54:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we have hearts\Nin rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.90,0:54:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much\Nthat's kind of a symbol of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.74,0:54:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our enduring love for you\Nvery good
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.62,0:54:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Ncan you put peanut butter on one side
