Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.54,1:44:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.38,1:44:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NGrant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, the courage to change the
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.30,1:44:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things I can, and the wisdom to know the difference.\NAmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.10,1:45:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat was great.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.62,1:45:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you both.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.68,1:45:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to watch the time.\NHoney.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.46,1:45:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to watch the time.\NDo you know what time it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.67,1:45:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe're past.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.49,1:45:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NWe're past, but we can go on, because they said we could finish up real quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.85,1:45:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NI was just wondering if you could give me your significance on an experience I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.61,1:45:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for like a split second, I convinced my mind that I was in a different body.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.83,1:45:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was like for a split second, and that happened twice, actually.\NI was just wondering what...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.73,1:46:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's horrific.\NHorrific?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.88,1:46:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTeach me how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.24,1:46:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you do that?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.35,1:46:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I tried doing it with my cat another time, but it didn't work.\NBy location.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.23,1:46:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just an interesting psychic.\NIt's a psychic phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.39,1:46:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A psychic.\NThat's spiritual psychic.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.09,1:46:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.\NIt's fun anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.15,1:46:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No significance behind it?\NJust that, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.13,1:46:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's harmless, yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.61,1:46:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I get a blessing from both of you?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.37,1:46:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A double blessing?\NGod bless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.97,1:46:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.03,1:46:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And God bless the innocence of your experience.\NPoor Dermot.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.06,1:46:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to sign.\NI can't see very well at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.58,1:46:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to sign things, you know.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.64,1:46:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI'm Jim, and this is Jerry.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.40,1:47:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're from Denver.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.76,1:47:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to relate a story to you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.06,1:47:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd Jerry's going to relate a story to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.32,1:47:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYour books have been life-changing for us, as well as those around us.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.90,1:47:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe have a friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.28,1:47:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We met him at a coffee shop.\NJim's been reading your books.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.50,1:47:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave him the book.\NPower Versus Force.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.34,1:47:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Power Versus Force.\NHe didn't read it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.04,1:47:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He flew on a plane to Manila.\NHe goes there for three months out of the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.08,1:47:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He read it on the plane.\NHe met a gentleman in Manila who is one of the chief negotiators for the Philippine government
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.84,1:47:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with Abu Sayyid.\NHe loved the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.26,1:47:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He ordered five more copies and is going with the team, negotiating team, with the terrorists\Nin the southern part of the Philippines with your books as guides.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.76,1:47:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.76,1:47:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.46,1:48:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.82,1:48:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.82,1:48:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick question.\NI've often heard you say that there's no identity in enlightenment where you're sitting.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.48,1:48:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't an identity there.\NAnd I'm curious as a student.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.02,1:48:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How?\NWhat is an appropriate?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.02,1:48:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or useful way to relate to the persona of Dr. Hawkins?\NDon't get attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.44,1:48:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's transitory.\NIt's pragmatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.44,1:49:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pragmatic.\NIt's pragmatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.08,1:49:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also arbitrary.\NI could also say the world needs another spiritual teacher like a hole in the head and quit it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.88,1:49:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel no loss.\NI could take the opposite view and say God blessed me with certain realizations.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.22,1:49:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That are helpful to share with others and feel an obligation.\NSo the reason I became a teacher is I chose the latter.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.09,1:49:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That the gift was given to me and I didn't need to teach.\NI was by myself in a state of bliss, infinite bliss, beyond time, place, and location.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.37,1:49:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'd have to retrack again how that all came about.\NThe obligation of becoming a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.85,1:49:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to write power versus force.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.49,1:49:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because remember, we were discussing it and I said you need to write this down so someone\Nwould.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.49,1:50:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she told me to write it down.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.45,1:50:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NI just kept it to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.45,1:50:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, gee, you really ought to share this and write it down.\NI said, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.45,1:50:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.45,1:50:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NAnd then we went back into the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.45,1:50:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnd then we spent every weekend traveling.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.45,1:50:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent all our life in.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.57,1:50:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.57,1:50:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.57,1:50:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.57,1:50:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.63,1:50:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.63,1:50:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.63,1:50:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.63,1:50:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.63,1:50:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.63,1:50:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.63,1:50:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.63,1:50:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.63,1:50:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.63,1:50:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.63,1:50:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.63,1:50:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.63,1:50:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.63,1:50:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NPlanes.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.63,1:50:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Planes.\NCharter, yeah, the Bill of Rights.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.03,1:51:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI have permission to calibrate the bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.23,1:51:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it, Bill Charter of Rights?\NYes, the Charter of Rights and Freedoms.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.31,1:51:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to calibrate that.\NIt calibrates over 480, 490, 495.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.24,1:51:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at 495, over 495.\NIt calibrates at 495.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.32,1:51:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very high, yes.\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.42,1:51:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reading it today, actually, and it doesn't mention God,\Nand that's probably one of the reasons why it doesn't calibrate high.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.12,1:51:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What, what did you say?\NIt doesn't mention God, did it?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.84,1:51:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NSo that could be why it doesn't calibrate as high.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.34,1:51:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 500, yeah.\NThank you both.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.69,1:51:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as well Canada stays away from God.\NYou see all the trouble it brings you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.38,1:51:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to have a place to escape.\NAt least Canada, you can escape God.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.64,1:51:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.36,1:52:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In my work in the world,\NI'm an herbalist in the Oriental medical tradition.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.65,1:52:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd through reading your books,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.63,1:52:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been inspired to, as I'm with a patient,\Nalso just simply love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.65,1:52:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NAnd I was wondering,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.63,1:52:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,apart from simply generating that quality of love for who I'm with,\Nif you recommend a certain method like a visualization.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.65,1:52:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, I've recited the Medicine Buddha Mantra\Nbecause that's part of my training.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.87,1:52:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.03,1:52:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.65,1:52:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.69,1:52:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.73,1:52:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.81,1:52:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.89,1:52:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.17,1:52:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.25,1:52:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.29,1:52:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.33,1:52:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.37,1:52:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.41,1:52:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.45,1:52:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.49,1:52:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIf you had any advice for me
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.19,1:52:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to benefit my patients more through the love principle.\NWell, I think it's just your intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.03,1:52:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your intention.\NYou know, it came to the end of my practice, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.45,1:52:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the insurance cost more than I wasn't making enough to pay the insurance.\NBut I couldn't stop practice because there were a couple of guys
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.25,1:52:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that were hanging on really because of their relationship with me.\NAnd I thought, geez, I can't desert these guys at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.75,1:53:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they've come all this way.\NAnd they've only got a half a mile left to go anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.83,1:53:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured I'll hang out with them until they leave.\NWhen they leave, then I'll close my practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.88,1:53:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they left the body, I closed my practice.\NSo it was just caring about them to realize what you mean to them
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.38,1:53:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and to fulfill that meaning.\NNow, if they were in psychoanalysis, it'd be different.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.28,1:53:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were in psychoanalysis, you would analyze out the positive transference.\NNow, these people, the positive transference is what was keeping them going.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.28,1:53:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember one old guy.\NGeez, he was funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.52,1:53:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, I want a picture of you, Doc.\NI put it on the wall because when I look at it, I feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.24,1:53:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, oh, okay.\NBut he and his wife would fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.54,1:54:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And she wouldn't allow him to drive the car because he was too senile.\NSo he would go into a screaming fit that she wouldn't let him drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.79,1:54:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So one day, he got the car.\NHe took the keys to the car, and he drove, and he got lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.30,1:54:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And he called me.\NI said, tell your wife to come and get you.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.86,1:54:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, God damn it.\NHe says, okay, Mildred, I get the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.69,1:54:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NNo, you care about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.92,1:54:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the caringness is transmitted, you know.\NThe caringness, the energy of the caringness is carried over to the patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.30,1:54:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say, I care about you.\NThat would scare them.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.20,1:54:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But your caringness.\NIs your power with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.64,1:54:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the healer is somebody who really cares about his patients.\NHe cares for their highest good, including preventing them from becoming
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.14,1:54:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,neurotically dependent on you.\NSo this old guy who felt better when he looked at my picture, because of his age,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.00,1:55:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to analyze that positive transference because it's keeping him alive.\NIf he was younger, I'd say, you know, you're projecting magic onto me.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.66,1:55:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your will to get better and your will to live that's energizing,\Nyou're functioning, not me, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.94,1:55:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.16,1:55:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it depends on the patient, the relationship, the phase,\Nand what it is you're trying to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.25,1:55:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.41,1:55:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you also, Susan.\NThank you, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.38,1:55:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't hurt to pray for a patient.\NI used to pray for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.60,1:55:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, God, if you don't mind it, I hope Mac gets better.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.32,1:55:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to bother God with all kinds of stuff, you know what I'm saying?\NWatch out.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.31,1:55:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.19,1:55:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to look into your eyes and experience you closer than back there in the back of the room.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.49,1:56:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have a question about something that happened to me quite a while ago.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.35,1:56:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was probably about 25 or so.\NI started going to a meditation class, and they talked about love.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.07,1:56:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, well, I don't know what that feels like.\NAnd so I meditated on love every day for about a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.95,1:56:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NBut what happened was, all of a sudden, I was leaving.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.79,1:56:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, life was shit, but all of a sudden, I felt what love felt like, and I was leaving.\NIf this is what it feels like, I'm going to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.21,1:56:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know what you mean.\NWell, my life just rolled in front of me, and I realized that wasn't a failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:49.59,1:56:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NEverything was a failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.21,1:56:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I'd done was a total success, and that's the only way it could have ever been.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.78,1:57:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Recontextualize the whole thing, yeah.\NSo I decided to come back because I had more to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.64,1:57:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo my question is, what did that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.51,1:57:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How far did that go?\NIs there something way past that in consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.57,1:57:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Way past what?\NLove.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.83,1:57:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.\NNo, the ultimate love resolves all differentiation of a this from a that, or a me and a you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.77,1:57:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it merges into, what's the right word for it, of divinity.\NIt merges into divinity in which there is no me and you, or this and a that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.83,1:57:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.47,1:58:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you for all your writings, and your map is just amazing.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.40,1:58:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NHow much time we got left?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:05.00,1:58:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We better, I better watch it.\NYeah, we're all done.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.94,1:58:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're over.\NI think we're over the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.72,1:58:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now, doctor's going to shake everyone's hand in the audience.\NOh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.62,1:58:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need you to either come down, either the center aisles, because you cannot come down this outside aisle.\NSo if you could come down the center aisles and come across the front of the stage, he'll be over here, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.42,1:58:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that where he's going to be?\NI have to have a soda.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.78,1:58:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be over here in the corner.\NAnd then you can file up this aisle to go out.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:37.52,1:58:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But he will try and shake everybody's hands here in the auditoriums, if that's all right.\NWhere's my coffee, honey?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.34,1:58:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Coffee?\NJust a minute.
